docs.lead_paragraph: PALMER, Alaska — For years, pet owners in this Anchorage suburb of big homes and lawns have fretted over snares set in the local parks by fur-trappers going after fox, lynx and rabbits. But in a quiet revolution this spring, dog lovers got the upper hand, and after a series of public meetings where few trappers showed up to fight back, trapping was banned by the borough council. The suburbs had won.

headline.main: Alaska Warily Eyes Change Bringing Suburbs and Amazon Boxes
headline.print_headline: Go-It-Alone Alaska Is Wary as Change Brings World Closer

docs.lead_paragraph: All film lovers, amateur and professional, no matter how well-versed, have gaps in their movie knowledge.
